<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Beautiful Pleasure Wins Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Beautiful Pleasure, enjoying an  
11-pound weight concession, went to the front early and then held 
off favored Banshee Breeze by 2 1/4 lengths Friday to win the 
$400,000, Grade I Personal Ensign Handicap at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Jorge Chavez and carrying 113 pounds, Beautiful  
Pleasure still led by five lengths with a furlong to go in the 
1 1/4-mile race that was run on a muddy track. 
</P>
<P>
	Banshee Breeze finished 1 1/2 lengths in front of Keeper Hill,  
while Manoa, Tap to Music and Unbridled Hope completed the order of 
finish. 
</P>
<P>
	Beautiful Pleasure and Banshee Breeze last met in the Go For  
Wand Handicap at Saratoga on Aug. 7. The race was a furlong longer 
and the weight difference the same, but Banshee Breeze prevailed by 
a half-length. 
</P>
<P>
	``The weight just broke the bridge today,'' said Carl Nafzger,  
Banshee Breeze's trainer. ``It was very muddy out there. At least, 
she beat all the others.'' 
</P>
<P>
	John Ward, Beautiful Pleasure's trainer, credited the early lead  
for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think they had much choice but to let her be on the  
lead,'' he said. ``She has a nice, long stride and a light weight. 
Nobody could chase her; they could just pray that she didn't have 
enough strength to finish it up. It all comes down to timing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Beautiful Pleasure covered 1 1/4 miles in 2:02:2 and earned  
$240,000 for John C. Oxley with her second win in five starts this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $11.40, $4.30 and $2.90. Banshee Breeze paid  
$2.70 and $2.10, while Keeper Hill was $2.80 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
