<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Activity Trays Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Some 100,000 activity trays and toy nets were  
recalled Friday because four small children have choked on suction 
cups used to attach them to surfaces. 
</P>
<P>
	The Consumer Product Safety Commission recalled the trays and  
nets -- the Stroller Snack and Activity Trays, Bathtime Activity 
Trays and Bathtime Toy Netting -- sold by Graco Children's Products 
and Children on the Go. The commission said children can easily 
detach the suction cups and choke on them. 
</P>
<P>
	Graco has received reports of four choking incidents, one each  
in Wisconsin and Ohio and two in New York, said commission 
spokeswoman Nychelle Fleming. In the Ohio incident, the suction cup 
was dislodged from the throat of a 7-month-old. 
</P>
<P>
	The recalled items can be used with toys from the Mix 'N Move  
line and attached to strollers, bath tub tiles or other smooth 
surfaces. They were sold nationwide at discount, department and toy 
stores from January 1998 until this month for $10 to $15 each. 
</P>
<P>
	Consumers should call (800) 446-1366 to receive a free repair  
kit that will permanently attach the suction cups to the trays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
