<HEADLINE> Cover Gal Scores at Del Mar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Cover Gal, ridden by Kent Desormeaux,  
moved in front early and went on to take a three-length victory in 
Friday's $107,800 Generous Portion Stakes at Del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
	A winner at 22-1 odds in her debut on July 31, Cover Gal was  
sent off as the 1-5 favorite this time. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner fought off a challenge by Excessively Hot in the  
upper stretch, then pulled away in the 5 1/2-furlong race for 
2-year-old fillies bred in California. 
</P>
<P>
	Cover Gal carried 117 pounds and was clocked in 1:04 2-5 in the  
feature race run before a crowd of 13,908. 
</P>
<P>
	Excessively Hot finished second, 3 1/2 lengths in front of Wingless  
Flight, in the race contested by seven fillies. 
</P>
<P>
	Cover Gal, a daughter of Falstaff and Video Menu, paid $2.40,  
$2.20 and $2.10. Excessively Hot returned $2.60 and $2.10, and the 
show payoff on Wingless Flight was $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by Bill Peeples and trained by Lance Stokes, Cover Gal  
earned $64,680. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
