<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Downey Jr. Back in Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CORCORAN, Calif. (AP) -- Robert Downey Jr. is back behind bars.  
</P>
<P>
	Downey, 34, arrived Thursday at Corcoran State Prison, where he  
will be housed with other inmates in a dormitory setting, said 
prison spokeswoman Belle Call. He'll be treated at the prison 
substance abuse unit, along with about 7,000 other inmates. 
</P>
<P>
	Asked if the actor will receive special treatment, Call  
responded: ``Negative. He's an inmate. That's what he is to us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this month, Municipal Judge Lawrence Mira sentenced  
Downey to three years for a probation violation stemming from a 
1996 drug conviction. The judge refused the actor's request to 
remain on parole, saying Downey had manipulated doctors and 
psychiatrists during seven court-ordered drug rehabilitation 
programs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
