<HEADLINE> E-mail Calls You a 'Big Stupid Jerk' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japan's Fuji Bank Ltd. inadvertently sent out a  
virus-tainted e-mail that makes computers display a message calling 
the recipient a ``big stupid jerk,'' the bank said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The bug was transmitted last week to investors worldwide via a  
memo detailing Fuji Bank's alliance with two other major Japanese 
banks, spokesman Hiroshi Takahashi said. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident did not damage computers, and the bank has  
apologized to all recipients, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The virus, which also changed some of the names in the memo to  
``Dr. Mountain Dew,'' was sent from a personal computer temporarily 
in use by the company, Takahashi said. 
</P>
<P>
	He added that the bank had ``done everything'' to eliminate the  
problem. 
</P>
<P>
	Fuji announced last week it would merge with Industrial Bank of  
Japan Ltd. and Dai-Ichi Kangyo Bank Ltd. in the fall of 2000 to 
form the world's largest financial operation. 
  	   	
</P>
