<HEADLINE> Report: Frankel Companion Calls Ex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- A man who says his ex-wife has been  
traveling with fugitive financier Martin Frankel said she called 
this week from Brazil, The Hartford Courant reported today. 
</P>
<P>
	Carlos Gustavo said his former wife, Adriana Gustavo, called  
Wednesday and said she and Frankel had been in Sao Paolo recently. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities have reportedly been concentrating their search for  
Frankel in Europe, where they believe he fled in May after 
allegedly bilking millions of dollars from insurance companies. 
Estimates of the losses have ranged from $50 million to as much as 
$3 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Frankel, a 44-year-old money manager who had a mansion in  
Greenwich, reportedly lived in Rome for several weeks in May and 
June before authorities began searching for him. 
</P>
<P>
	Adriana Gustavo, who is Brazilian, is described by friends as a  
one-time companion and employee of Frankel's. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know exactly where she was calling from, but she said  
Marty was no longer with her,'' said Gustavo, whose marriage fell 
apart in 1995 after his wife met Frankel. 
</P>
<P>
	Gustavo said that she did not leave a phone number where she  
could be reached. He said he telephoned a law enforcement agency to 
tell them about the call. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
