<HEADLINE> Fredericks Pulls Out of 200 Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEVILLE, Spain (AP) -- Former world champion Frankie Fredericks  
withdrew from the final of the 200 meters at the World 
Championships today, citing a left hamstring injury. 
</P>
<P>
	The Namibian sprinter, who owns nine medals from the Olympics  
and Worlds, had also pulled out of his semifinal heat for the 100 
on Sunday, but then returned to the Estadio Olimpico track for the 
200 heats. 
</P>
<P>
	Fredericks's withdrawal, coupled with the absence of defending  
world champion Ato Boldon because of an injury, left 100-meter gold 
winner Maurice Greene the favorite in the 200 final, slated for 
tonight. 
  	   	
</P>
