<HEADLINE> FedEx Closes Office in Antigua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. JOHN'S, Antigua (AP) -- Shipping company Federal Express has  
closed its office in Antigua amid an employee protest on sick pay. 
</P>
<P>
	The Memphis, Tennessee-based company is continuing to do  
business in Antigua and Barbuda with a local agent called Parcel 
Plus, Federal Express spokeswoman Jennifer McGowan said Friday. She 
said she could not elaborate on the office closing or disputes with 
employees. 
</P>
<P>
	In a letter Wednesday, local law firm Commodore and Associates  
issued a statement on behalf of the company confirming the office 
closed that day. Office employees lost their jobs and will receive 
severance pay, the statement said. It did not say how many were 
employed at the office. 
</P>
<P>
	Employees walked off the job last week to protest what they say  
was the company's refusal to give sick pay benefits to three 
employees. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
