<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mutiny 2, Crew 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Raul Diaz Arce scored his 11th goal of the  
season as the Tampa Bay Mutiny beat the Columbus Crew 2-1 Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	Diaz Arce put the Mutiny up 2-0 on a 2-on-1 break in the 48th  
minute, taking a pass from Manny Lagos, who had two assists. 
</P>
<P>
	Ritchie Kotschau scored for Tampa Bay in the 29th minute, while  
Robert Warzycha had Columbus' goal on a 25-yard free kick during 
the 71st minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Kotschau's second goal of the season came from 15 yards and was  
his second in three games. Tampa Bay's Musa Shannon, who has 11 
goals, missed the contest with a right knee strain. 
</P>
<P>
	Tampa Bay swept the MLS home-and-home series. The Mutiny posted  
a 2-1 shootout win last Sunday at Columbus. Thirteen of the 16 
games ever played between the teams have been decided by one goal. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
