today she was hopeful Israel and the Palestinians will conclude a 
long-sought agreement that would turn over more of the West Bank to 
Yasser Arafat's Palestinian Authority. Albright was upbeat after a 
firsthand report from Palestinian negotiator Saeb Erekat and 
Arafat's deputy, Mahmoud Abbas, widely known as Abu Mazen. ``I 
think we are looking forward to the conclusion of this aspect of 
the peace process,'' she said. 

</P>
<P>
	FCC Order Updates Authorities  
</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The government announced rules today that will  
give the FBI and other law enforcement agencies new electronic 
surveillance capabilities, enabling them to keep up with such 
technology as cellular phones and conference calls. The Federal 
Communications Commission's order, implementing a 1994 law, will 
let police and other authorities obtain a cellular phone user's 
location at the beginning and end of a call -- as long as a court 
approves. 

</P>
