<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Calif. Officials Find $80M in Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAKE ARROWHEAD, Calif. (AP) -- Agents have seized $80 million  
worth of marijuana -- 23,000 plants -- in a remote section of the San 
Bernardino National Forest, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers found the plants on a four-acre plantation near Lake  
Arrowhead, sheriff's spokesman Chip Patterson said Thursday. No 
arrests have been made, 
</P>
<P>
	``It's by far the largest growing operation we've ever seen in  
terms of sheer numbers. It took a couple dozen deputies two days to 
cut down all the plants,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The plantation, hidden by heavy brush and inaccessible by road,  
was discovered several weeks ago by deputies patrolling the area by 
helicopter. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers watched the area for two weeks, then seized the plants  
Tuesday, hoping also to capture six to eight men believed to have 
been living in tents and harvesting the crop. 
</P>
<P>
	``We think the suspects fled shortly before we arrived. They may  
have heard us coming,'' Patterson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Because of the remoteness of the location, law enforcement  
officials had to be airlifted in by helicopter. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
