<HEADLINE> Auburn Receiver Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Auburn receiver Clifton Robinson, who  
pleaded guilty earlier this month to a reduced charge of 
contributing to the delinquency of a minor, has been suspended from 
the Sept. 4 season opener against Appalachian State. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson was originally suspended from the team last spring,  
when he was charged with second-degree rape after allegedly having 
sex with a 15-year-old girl. 
</P>
<P>
	He avoided a trial by pleading guilty to the misdemeanor charge  
earlier this month and was ordered to serve 200 hours of community 
service. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Tommy Tuberville welcomed him back to the team after the  
plea agreement, but said he was considering some sort of punishment 
for the junior receiver. He decided Thursday to suspend him for one 
game. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson led the Tigers last year in all-purpose yards with 943.  
He was also second on the team with 42 catches for 672 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
