<HEADLINE> Heyns Breaks Breaststroke Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Penny Heyns of South Africa broke the  
world record for the women's 50-meter breaststroke at the Pan 
Pacific swimming championships on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Heyns was clocked in 30.83 seconds, breaking her record of 30.95  
set at the Goodwill Games in New York last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Heyns swam alone in a special time trial which meet officials  
said had been approved for a record attempt. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Heyns' eighth record in 11 swims at the Pan Pacific.  
  	   	
