<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Karsay Joins Indians DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Steve Karsay, who a week ago appeared to be the  
Indians' pitching savior, was placed on the 15-day disabled list 
Friday because of a strained tendon in his right forearm. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's more of a preventive thing than anything,'' Indians  
manager Mike Hargrove said. ``Every indication we've gotten from 
our doctors is that Steve will come back as strong as ever.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Karsay began the season as the Indians' long reliever, going 8-1  
with a 2.66 ERA in 42 appearances. But after injuries put Dwight 
Gooden, Jaret Wright and Mark Langston on the disabled list, the 
Indians moved Karsay, who began his career as a starter, into the 
rotation. 
</P>
<P>
	He went 2-0 with a 0.90 ERA in two starts, and Hargrove hinted  
that Karsay might be put in Cleveland's postseason rotation. 
</P>
<P>
	But that all changed Wednesday night in Oakland, when Karsay's  
forearm tightened and he was forced to leave after three innings. 
</P>
<P>
	``Steve was ready,'' Hargrove said. ``This was something he  
wanted to do and looked forward to doing. I'm the one who made the 
call to move him to the starting rotation because we had a need 
because of our injuries. I think it was a logical move, a logical 
transition and for whatever reason, it didn't work.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hargrove isn't convinced Karsay's injury was a result of  
overworking his right arm. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is not a serious problem,'' Hargrove said. ``Steve has a  
history of arm problems. We were very aware of that and cognizant 
of the risk. Steve was more than ready to assume that (starter's) 
role. It just didn't work.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Karsay, whose 10-game winning streak is the longest in the  
majors this season and the longest by an Indians pitcher since 
1975, will return to the bullpen once he's activated, Hargrove 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	To fill Karsay's roster spot, the Indians recalled left-handed  
reliever Tom Martin from Triple-A Buffalo. 
</P>
<P>
	With Karsay on the DL for the second time this season -- he was  
out from July 2-26 with a strained side muscle -- the Indians have 
nine players on the disabled list, including four starters. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
