<HEADLINE> Calif. Suspect Refuses Hair Sample </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- A handyman charged with beheading a  
Yosemite National Park naturalist and suspected in the deaths of 
three tourists is refusing to give samples of his blood, hair and 
saliva. 
</P>
<P>
	Cary Stayner's lawyer filed papers in federal court Thursday  
saying prosecutors should not be allowed to obtain the samples 
without a search warrant and have not provided evidence that such a 
warrant is justified. 
</P>
