<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Friday, Aug. 27, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Stocks Fall After Greenspan Warning  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks fell today after Federal Reserve Chairman  
Alan Greenspan voiced concern over the highly valued stock market, 
striking fear in investors who interpreted the remarks as a sign 
the Fed isn't finished raising rates. The Dow Jones industrial 
average was down 108.28 to 11,090.17, the second straight day the 
Dow lost more than 100 points. Broader stock indicators were also 
lower today. Declining issues on the New York Stock Exchange led 
advancers 1,765-1,113. The Nasdaq was down 15.73 to 2,758.89. 

</P>
