<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Air Force Captain Admits to Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OFFUTT AIR FORCE BASE, Neb. (AP) -- An Air Force captain will  
serve four months in a military jail after admitting to having sex 
with two enlisted women, including one he later married. 
</P>
<P>
	Capt. Douglas Bass pleaded guilty to lying to an investigator  
and disobeying orders to end his relationship with Krystal Carr, 
now his wife. 
</P>
<P>
	Bass pleaded guilty to nine counts of violating military law.  
After serving his four-month sentence, he will be dismissed -- an 
officer's equivalent to a dishonorable discharge, his attorney 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bass was the commanding officer over Carr and her first husband  
when their affair started in 1998, shortly after Carr's husband was 
deployed to Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
<P>
	Military officials learned about the affair in February 1999 and  
ordered Bass to end it, but he denied the relationship. 
</P>
<P>
	Carr also refused to end the affair and she was convicted of  
violating military law. She served 50 days of a 60-day sentence and 
was released early for good behavior in May. 
</P>
<P>
	Bass also had a relationship with an unidentified staff sergeant  
at Barksdale Air Force Base in Louisiana before he met Carr. The 
woman wasn't under his command. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
