<HEADLINE> Devil Rays Place Eiland on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Devil Rays placed  
pitcher Dave Eiland on the disabled list with left hip bursitis 
Friday and recalled reliever Alan Newman from Triple-A Durham. 
</P>
<P>
	Eiland, 4-7 with a 5.48 ERA, left Thursday's game against the  
Chicago White Sox in the third inning with hip soreness. The stint 
on the DL is the second of the season for the right-hander, who 
missed part of June because of lower back stiffness. 
</P>
<P>
	Eiland had won three of his past five starts, getting his first  
victories in consecutive decisions for the first time since 
September 1990 with the New York Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
	Newman, a left-handed reliever, has been with the Devil Rays on  
four different occasions this season, going 1-2 with a 10.13 ERA in 
six games. 
</P>
