<HEADLINE> Jury To Consider Stephen King Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SOUTH PARIS, Maine (AP) -- A grand jury will consider the case of  
a driver whose van struck and injured Stephen King. 
</P>
<P>
	The June 19 accident was investigated by the sheriff's  
department, which turned over its report to the district attorney. 
</P>
<P>
	District Attorney Norman Croteau said Friday the Oxford County  
grand jury will decide whether Bryan Smith will be charged. The 
grand jury begins its session Sept. 30. Croteau wouldn't comment 
further. 
</P>
<P>
	King, 51, was walking along the shoulder of a road near his  
vacation home when he was hit by the van. He has undergone several 
surgeries to set broken bones in his leg and hip and faces a long 
rehabilitation. 
</P>
<P>
	A sheriff's deputy quoted Smith, who has a history of driving  
offenses, as saying he was distracted by a dog in his van and ran 
off the road. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
