<HEADLINE> Compaq To Lay Off 1,600 in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SINGAPORE (AP) -- In the latest wave of layoffs to hit  
Singapore's electronics industry, U.S. computer maker Compaq will 
lay off 1,600 people, or nearly two-thirds of the workers at its 
Singapore factory, the company said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The world's largest personal computer maker announced in July  
that it would close a number of plants and slash up to 8,000 jobs 
worldwide to reverse financial losses. Compaq reported an $184 
million loss in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	In Singapore, Compaq plans to complete the staff cuts by the  
first quarter of next year, according to Wong King Yoong, vice 
president and managing director of Compaq Asia. 
</P>
<P>
	Compaq is based in Houston, Texas.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
