<HEADLINE> Greg Manning Hired as Georgia St AD </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Greg Manning, a former Maryland basketball star,  
was hired as athletic director at Georgia State on Thursday, 
reuniting him with his former coach, Lefty Driesell. 
</P>
<P>
	Manning, 39, spent the past five years as director of major  
gifts at his alma mater. His hiring by Georgia State ended a 
three-month search for a successor to Orby Moss, who resigned after 
nine years to take a similar position at Norfolk State. 
</P>
<P>
	Manning was an academic All-American and four-year starter at  
Maryland from 1978-81, playing for Driesell. 
</P>
<P>
	``I know Greg, but I wasn't involved in the selection process,''  
said Driesell, preparing for his third season at Georgia State. 
``Of course, they asked me about him. He's a great young man who is 
well respected at Maryland.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Georgia State wanted someone with a strong fund-raising  
background to be the school's fifth AD. During Maryland's 1998-99 
budget year, Manning was responsible for raising $1.2 million in 
cash and $300,000 in scholarship endowments for the athletic 
program. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
