<HEADLINE> Utah Jazz Names Personnel Director </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- The Utah Jazz will sign veteran free-agent  
center Olden Polynice to a two-year deal, Polynice's agent said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	Polynice, 34, was in Salt Lake City taking a physical this  
morning, according to agent Dwight Manley, who said a news 
conference to announce the deal will likely be held later in the 
day. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm going up there in an hour. We plan on signing,'' Manley  
said this morning. 
</P>
<P>
	Manley, who is also the agent for Jazz forward Karl Malone,  
would not disclose the terms of the deal, but said it was a 
two-year contract with an option for a third year. 
</P>
<P>
	Polynice, 34, averaged eight points and nine rebounds per game  
for Seattle last year. 
</P>
<P>
	It will be the second major move for the Jazz in 24 hours.  
Yesterday, the team concluded a two-week search by hiring Kevin 
O'Connor as the new vice president of basketball operations. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Connor, director of player personnel for the Philadelphia  
76ers last year, succeeds Scott Layden, who left Aug. 10 to become 
general manager of the New York Knicks. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Connor, 51, said he planned to start with the Jazz ``as soon  
as I can clean out my desk in Philadelphia,'' although he expected 
to work for both organizations during the transition. 
  	   	
