<HEADLINE> Szabo Wins 5,000m Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEVILLE, Spain (AP) -- Gabriela Szabo of Romania extended her  
reign over the 5,000 meters at the World Championships today, 
beating Zahra Ouaziz of Morocco with a championship record. 
Averlech Worku of Ethiopia finished third. 
</P>
<P>
	Szabo swept past Ouaziz with a finishing kick some 250 meters  
from the finish line and crossed in 14 minutes 41.82 seconds, 
improving on the mark of 14:46.47 Sonia O'Sullivan of Britain had 
set to win the 1995 title in Goteborg. 
</P>
<P>
	Ouaziz took the silver with 14:43.15 and Worku finished in  
14:44.22. 
</P>
<P>
	Szabo is the 3,000 specialist and only ran her first 5,000 of  
the season in a qualifying heat for the World Championships. She 
has yet to be beaten this year and defeated Ouaziz for the 12th 
time in a row since 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 3,000, the Romanian is still going for a share of the $1  
million Golden League jackpot after notching her fifth win in a row 
in Zurich two weeks ago, where she beat Ouaziz. 
</P>
<P>
	Today, Szabo took the early lead, setting a pace only three  
rivals could match, Ouaziz took over around the half-way mark, 
desperately trying to shake off her main opponent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Moroccan increased her pace again with three laps to go and  
only Szabo and Worku could stay in her wake. 
</P>
<P>
	When Szabo put in her finishing rush no one could match her.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
